Modifications for the ShantiLipi project include:
- Subsetting to Bengali + Vedic Extensions
- ba/va distinction (U+09F0 conjunct rules cloned from U+09AC)
- Removal of non-standard _ya_trad ligatures for standard Bengali য-phala rendering
- Addition of হ্ন conjunct support via psts feature
- Scaled and repositioned Vedic accent marks (udatta, anudatta, double svarita)
- Matra-aware GPOS mark positioning (clears ি ী ৈ ৌ above, ু ূ ৃ র-phala below)
- Added anudatta to MarkToBase lookup for Bengali consonant bases
- Em dash and en dash inclusion
- Adjusted line metrics for Vedic mark headroom
- Font renaming and metadata updates
